reviews.text: Still in the soft opening phase.  Prices are inline with the area.   Good food and friendly staff.

Came across this new Kappo-style Japanese restaurant in Tai Hang earlier this week.  I've tried the 1) Japanese tomato 2) sea urchin 3) foie gras chawanmushi 4) neck meat 5) zuwai croquette 6) kona wings 7) harami australian wagyu 8) pork belly & 9) wagyu beef bowl.  Food was great and with the friendly staff the overall experience was excellent.  Looking forward to returning and try other dishes on the menu.
